Zoho CRM MCP allows AI agents to perform CRM operations through the Model Context Protocol, enabling natural language interaction without manual API coding [1][2]. You can use either official, pre-built servers hosted by Zoho or community-developed open-source servers [1][3][4][5].

The official Zoho implementation provides four pre-built, hosted servers—Data Insights, Data Operations, Module Customization, and Workflow & Process Automation—which you connect by adding a generated URL to your AI client's configuration [5]. Alternatively, open-source community servers are available for self-hosting via Python or Node.js, providing comprehensive CRUD, search, and metadata management tools [3][4][6][7].

For clients like Claude Desktop, add the server details to your configuration file:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "zoho-crm": {
      "url": "https://<your-unique-zoho-mcp-server-url>"
    }
  }
}
```

Authentication is handled via OAuth, and operations are limited by your existing CRM user permissions [1][5].
